3 chanters (glamour of kintaz minimum) really made controlling the amag guys and their annoying pets easier.  <br>
FD puller that really knows the zone is essential.  It also helps on the DA pull to see what is coming, give chanters warning etc.<br>
<br>
I think we had almost 5 groups, overkill but all it takes is one minor screwup and the mob is gone essentially forever (never saw it up for 6 months till that time) <p>Don't use me for my mind.  I want you to respect me for my body.<br>
<br>
&lt;BR&gt;Hangovr Regrets<br>
&lt;BR&gt;Tank Mezzer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ghennaswordmaster>ghennaswordmaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#333333>(12/8/02 1:16:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wraith of shissar; POF pulling tips</span><hr size=1> Break the westwall first.. then make your way north to the ammy temple.  Make sure you pull all or most of the knights behind the firewall before you go for the wraith.  There should be 2 phoboplasms up next to shissar, and you can pull those without pulling shissar(since they are on seperate factions)<br>
<br>
If shissar happens to cast an ae spell next to other mobs .. since it is a druid mob and on a different faction /wave shissar.  <br>
<br>
Big thing if you are doing this with a small number of people.  Make sure to ditch the people under 55 or there will be adds comming from the other side of the zone.<br>
<br>
I did shissar with full spawn fear with 1 solid group(war,cle,enc,enc,rng,dru) and the other enchanter was either dead the whole time or linkdead.  He was only 52 so i think it helped us out =p<br>
<br>
